  "prompt": "Who invented the concept of money?",
  "response": "The concept of money has evolved over thousands of years, making it difficult to attribute its invention to a single person or civilization. Early forms of exchange included:\n\n1. Bartering (prehistoric times)\n2. Commodity money (using valuable items like salt, cattle, or shells)\n3. Metal coins (around 600 BCE in Lydia, modern-day Turkey)\n4. Paper currency (China, during the Tang Dynasty, around 700 CE)\n\nDifferent cultures developed monetary systems independently, with each civilization contributing to the concept's evolution. The Mesopotamians, Egyptians, Greeks, and Romans all had sophisticated monetary systems that influenced modern currency.\n\nThe modern concept of money as we know it today is the result of centuries of economic development and technological innovation, rather than a single invention by one person.",
